A gold bar from Anna! But it's hollow,
made from papier-mâché... The color
isn't very convincing, either.

A gold bar from Anna! But it's made
from gilded papier-mâché... And nearly
as heavy as the real thing.

A beautiful headpiece from Emmeryn.
The seemingly simple design has a
certain dignified elegance.

A beautiful headpiece from Emmeryn.
Its appearance reminds onlookers of a
saintly halo.

An armored headband from Say'ri.
Simple, but effective, with a metal
plate sewn on for protection.

An armored headband from Say'ri.
In Chon'sin culture, only nobles of
high status are allowed one.

A strong fake mustache from Mustafa.
The dignified whiskers demand the
respect of all. Doubles as a disguise.

A glorious fake beard from Mustafa.
The supreme fullness demands the
respect of all. Complicates eating.

A merchant who travels the Halidom of Ylisse.
She has many sisters who share both her face
and name. Appears in Fire Emblem Awakening.

Kind and loving Exalt who rules over the
Halidom of Ylisse. She is the sister of Chrom
and Lissa. Appears in Fire Emblem Awakening.

The upright and dignified princess of the
Chon'sin dynasty. She has a direct approach
and never forgives a crooked deed. Appears
in Fire Emblem Awakening.

The King of Plegia, who thirsts for battle.
Together with Aversa, he begins a war against
the Halidom of Ylisse. Appears in Fire Emblem
Awakening.

General of Plegia. He is endlessly loyal to his
king, but he is a military man who prefers a fair
fight to besting his foes through trickery.
Appears in Fire Emblem Awakening.

A ljósálfr from Ljósálfheimr, the realm of
dreams. She brings daydreams to mortals
and sleeps during day and night. Always
seems to have just woken up.
Kusakihara Toshiyuki (草木原俊行) / INTELLIGENT SYSTEMS

Mythic Effect: Anima
Boost: HP+5, Res+5

Grants allies this Mythic Effect during Anima
season, if the Anima blessing has been conferred
and if this unit enters battle in Aether Raids with
them: Anima-blessed allies decrease the
Aetheric Lift lost for defense failures during
Anima season. (This decrease is limited to the
number of Mythic Heroes (Max: 2) × the number
of Heroes with the blessing conferred × 5.)

During Anima season, this Mythic Hero will
decrease Aetheric Lift loss for defense
failures depending on number of merges. (This
decrease is limited to the number of times the
units have been merged × 1 (Max: 20).)

Effectively gets Atk+12 and Spd+16.
She can also move adjacent to any
ally within two spaces of her.

Has a damage-reducing skill and can
counterattack regardless of her foe's
range if her HP ≥ 50%.

Grants allies bonuses and extra action
while also weakening foes. Can further
weaken foes afflicted with Penalty.

Grants Atk+3. If unit’s Def ≥ foe’s Def+1, foe
cannot make a follow-up attack. If foe's
Range = 2, calculates damage using the
lower of foe's Def or Res.

If foe initiates combat, inflicts Atk-6 on foe
during combat.

Inflicts Spd-5. If unit initiates combat, unit attacks

foes within 2 spaces of target, and inflicts

At start of combat, if unit's HP ≥ 25% and

effects that guarantee foe's follow-up
attacks during combat.

At start of combat, if unit's HP ≥ 50%, grants

counterattack.

If unit initiates combat, grants Atk/Def+4

If unit is within 2 spaces of an ally, grants

$aGrants Res+3. If【Penalty】is active on any
foes within 3 columns centered on unit, inflicts
Atk/Def/Res-3 on those foes during combat.

【Penalty】
All effects that last "on foe through its next
action." Includes penalties inflicted by a skill
like Panic or Threaten and negative status
effects (preventing counterattacks, restricting
movement, or the effects of a skill like
Triangle Adept or Guard).

Accelerates Special trigger (cooldown count-1).
At start of combat, if unit's HP ≥ 50%, unit can
counterattack regardless of foe's range.

Grants Spd+3. Unit can move to a space
adjacent to an ally within 2 spaces. At start
of combat, if foe's HP ≥ 75%, grants
Atk/Spd+5 to unit during combat.

If foe initiates combat, grants Res+7 during
combat.

If foe initiates combat, grants Res+7 during
combat.

grants Atk/Spd/Def/Res+4 to unit and deals

Effect:【Dagger ７】

【Penalty】
All effects that last "on foe through its next
action." Includes penalties inflicted by a skill
like Panic or Threaten and negative status
effects (preventing counterattacks, restricting
movement, or the effects of a skill like
Triangle Adept or Guard).

【Dagger ７】
After combat, if unit attacked, inflicts
Def/Res-７ on target and foes within
2 spaces of target through their next actions.

Grants another action to target ally. Grants
Atk+5 to target ally and allies within 2 spaces
of target (excluding unit) for 1 turn. Inflicts
Atk-5 on nearest foes within 4 spaces of target
ally and any foe within 2 spaces of those foes
through their next actions. (Cannot target an
ally with Sing or Dance. This skill treated as
Sing or Dance.)

If foe initiates combat, grants Atk/Spd+6 during
combat and inflicts Special cooldown charge -1
on foe per attack. (Only highest value applied.
Does not stack.)

Grants Spd+4 to allies within 2 spaces during
combat. If unit is within 2 spaces of an ally,
grants Spd+4 to unit during combat.
